### 4. Entity-Relationship[ER] Modeling
- 
- Used before database creation
##### Entity Type:
- The description or classification of a particular group of members in a set of data.

##### Entity: Real world object
- The reference to the member itslef. Think of an object. Represented a  rectangles.

      Ex: Student
          Employee
          Product

##### Attributes: Properties
- Characterstics of entities. Represented by Ovals

        Student:
        ---------
        ID
        Name
        Age

##### Relationships
- A description on how two entities interact with each other in the database. represented as diamonds or labelled lines.

        Student
        |
        Enrolls
        |
        Courses

##### Cardinality
- It defines how many entities participate in a relationship.

    - ONE-TO-ONE (1:1): 
        One Entity instance relates to exactly one other.
        
            Person <=> Passport

    - ONE-TO-MANY (1:N):
        One entity instance relates to multiple others.

             Dept -> Employees
- MANY-TO-MANY (M:N)
        Multiple entity instances relates to multiple others.

        Students <=> Courses

